ions of cultural memory. Proposing an approach to mapping through decolonial aesthetics and poetic thinking, the three essays in this volume help define a film studies perspective on mapping as a practice that structures political and aesthetic regimes, organizes and communicates shared realities, but also enables dissenting reconfigurations of concretely experienced worlds.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picturesxEuropean influences. 0aMotion picturesxPhilosophy. 4aMapping. 4aPostcolonialismus. 4afilmisches Erlebnis. 4averkörperte Mobilitäten. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aMapping.  acinematic experience.  aembodied mobilities.  apostcolonialism.1 aCarter, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalcomess, Bettina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMalcomess, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRositzka, Eileen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRositzka, Eileen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831107690500 cprintz978311076898540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110769012zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110769012zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110769012/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA